### ================================================================
### 🔑 Hidden Gems SL — API Key Validation Tests
### VS Code REST Client Extension හරහා run කරන්න
### Extension: humao.rest-client
###
### 📌 How to Use:
###   1. ඔයාගේ real API keys පහළ @variables ගෙ fill කරන්න
###   2. Test කරන්නට "Send Request" click කරන්න (request ඉහළ "▶ Send Request" button)
###   3. ✅ = 200/OK, ❌ = 401/403 = Key invalid
### ================================================================

### ── 🔧 Variables (ඔයාගේ real keys මෙතෙන් දාන්න) ─────────────────
@gemini_api_key     = YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY_HERE
@weather_api_key    = YOUR_WEATHER_API_KEY_HERE
@tripme_api_key     = dev-key-local
@backend_url        = http://localhost:8000/api
@firebase_api_key   = YOUR_FIREBASE_API_KEY_HERE
@firebase_project   = YOUR_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID


### ================================================================
### 1️⃣  GEMINI API KEY TEST
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 + JSON with "candidates" field
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 400 = "API_KEY_INVALID" or "PERMISSION_DENIED"
### ================================================================

# @name gemini_key_test
POST https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-1.5-flash:generateContent?key={{gemini_api_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contents": [
    {
      "parts": [
        {
          "text": "Say hello in one word"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### ================================================================
### 2️⃣  WEATHER API KEY TEST (OpenWeatherMap)
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 + weather JSON
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 401 = {"cod":401, "message":"Invalid API key"}
### ================================================================

# @name weather_key_test
GET https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=Colombo&appid={{weather_api_key}}&units=metric

###

### ================================================================
### 3️⃣  FIREBASE AUTH — API KEY TEST
###    (Anonymous sign-in — key test කරන fastest ක්‍රමය)
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 + {"kind": "identitytoolkit..."}
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 400 = "INVALID_API_KEY"
### ================================================================

# @name firebase_key_test
POST https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com/v1/accounts:signUp?key={{firebase_api_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "returnSecureToken": true
}

###

### ================================================================
### 4️⃣  FIRESTORE — READ TEST (Firebase API key)
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 + Firestore collection data
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 403 = "PERMISSION_DENIED" (rules issue)
###               HTTP 400 = API key invalid
### ================================================================

# @name firestore_read_test
GET https://firestore.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{{firebase_project}}/databases/(default)/documents/gems?pageSize=1&key={{firebase_api_key}}

###

### ================================================================
### 5️⃣  BACKEND API (TripMe / Hidden Gems Backend) — KEY TEST
###    App config ගෙ `baseUrl` හරහා backend check
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 or 404 (server alive)
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 401 = "Unauthorized" (key wrong)
###               Connection refused = Server down
### ================================================================

# @name backend_health_test
GET {{backend_url}}/health
X-API-Key: {{tripme_api_key}}
X-Zenith-Version: 1.0

###

### ================================================================
### 6️⃣  BACKEND — AUTH ENDPOINT TEST
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 + valid response
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 401 = key invalid
### ================================================================

# @name backend_auth_test
POST {{backend_url}}/auth/validate
Content-Type: application/json
X-TripMe-Version: 1.0.0-Hardened

{
  "apiKey": "{{tripme_api_key}}",
  "clientVersion": "1.0.0"
}

###

### ================================================================
### 7️⃣  REVENUECAT — ANDROID KEY TEST
###    ✅ Success: HTTP 200 + subscriber info
###    ❌ Fail:    HTTP 401 = "This app does not exist"
###
### 📌 Note: RevenueCat keys test කරන්න subscriber ID දෙන්න ඕනේ
### ================================================================

@revenuecat_android_key = YOUR_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_KEY_HERE
@test_user_id           = test_user_001

# @name revenuecat_key_test
GET https://api.revenuecat.com/v1/subscribers/{{test_user_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{revenuecat_android_key}}
X-Platform: android
Content-Type: application/json

###

### ================================================================
### 🧪 QUICK STATUS SUMMARY — All At A Glance
###
### Expected Results:
###   ✅ Gemini:     200 OK  → API key valid
###   ✅ Weather:    200 OK  → API key valid
###   ✅ Firebase:   200 OK  → API key valid
###   ✅ Firestore:  200 OK  → API key valid + rules OK
###   ✅ Backend:    200 OK  → Server running, key accepted
###   ✅ RevenueCat: 200 OK  → Key valid
###
### Common Errors:
###   400 INVALID_API_KEY   → Key wrong/missing
###   401 Unauthorized      → Key wrong or missing header
###   403 PERMISSION_DENIED → Key valid but no access (rules/restrictions)
###   Connection refused    → Backend server not running
### ================================================================
